Read your note about the pronunciation problem. Mr. Read found that
there was difficulty in people from different countries understanding
each other due to their accents. For example, we could hardly be
expected to read a cockney accent in Shaws Alphabet. For written
material to yourself there is no problem at all. But, if you do have a
regional accent and want to correspond with people outside your region
then it would be obvious that you would have to conform to the standard
English pronunciation. This is a part of understanding how to use it on
a national or international scale. And, it is a courtesy on your part.
Checking out whether a reader could understand your particular accent
would be common sense. Good luck on your studies.
Sid Tanaban 


